Gauteng premier Panyaza Lesufi on Thursday confirmed that the death toll from the Boksburg explosion has risen to 40. “This number is inclusive of 12 health workers. Five are still in various hospitals,” he said, adding that 23 people who had sustained various injuries had been discharged. “Our report, as I have indicated, is based on  confirmed numbers but we know this  may change as we get more confirmations from the facilities.” TimesLIVE Support independent journalism by subscribing to the Sunday Times. Just R20 for the first month.